License: GPL (>= 3)
Copyright: Incorporates C++ code from 'FACT' (GPL-3, doi:10.1145/2925985) and,
  with permission, from 'FACT2' and 'FDCT' by Jesper Jansson and colleagues.
Description: Efficient construction of phylogenetic consensus trees from a set
  of input trees.  Methods include strict, majority-rule, majority-rule (+),
  loose (combinable component / semi-strict), greedy, Adams, frequency
  difference, R*, and local consensus, computed using asymptotically efficient
  algorithms.  Builds on 'TreeTools' for the manipulation of trees and splits.
URL: https://github.com/ms609/Consensus/
